name: Erin Fetherston
bio: Fashion & Interiors. Represented by @theeyeagency and @inkprgroup Book a 1:1 consult with me via @theexpert Shop my line exclusively @anthropologie

social_posts.post_text: V.1 of my primary bedroom! This fabulous bed from @jossandmain was such a great find (and it was in stock, so score!). Soon she will become the star of our guest room as we continue to shift things around as all our pieces arrive. This is a great example of my strategy for selecting fundamental furniture items like beds and sofas- I usually go neutral and choose something that can be styled in a variety of ways, giving it longevity in the home. Here she is decked out in my favorite, blush…but soon she will get a cozy bedding makeover- stay tuned. Photography by @elizabethmessina

I was pretty excited about this boucle glider from @crateandkids , not only because I’m obsessed with boucle but the taller back height gives me the full support I need while caring for baby. What do you look for in a glider?

If you’re looking for holiday gift ideas, @framebridge is one of my go-tos for beautiful, easy to execute, meaningful gifts. I’m still swooning over the gallery wall I did with them for our new home. Photo by @elizabethmessina

When asked to describe my personal home style, sometimes I joke that I just want to live inside a cloud. A key part of that is accomplished with window treatments. Case in point, the luxe linen tailored pleat drapes from @theshadestore in my living room frame the natural light in such an ethereal way, giving me all the dreamy feels. Couldn’t you just float away? #TheShadeStore #LoveYourWindows

I’m delighted to share my project for @hoopesvineyard @hoopesestategh is live on @housebeautiful today! Link in my stories!  This project was two years in the making and I’m so excited to give you the full tour, so stay tuned for lots of juicy design content! Scroll through for a kick-off peek of these historic exteriors we refreshed with the help of @benjaminmoore,  @serenaandlily and @timbertech  Design: Erin Fetherston  Photos: @elizabethmessina  Styling: @bethprotass
Welcome to Part I of my BTS tour of the @hoopesestategh as seen in @housebeautiful  This is my first reel ever, so let me know what you think!

I’m super excited to share all the nooks and crannies of my project for @hoopesestategh with you, starting with this custom carved door featuring the @hoopesvineyard “H” made for us by @simpsondoorco . So chic! Up next, the living room….photography by @elizabethmessina styling by @bethprotass

Here we are in the living room of the @hoopesestategh . My intention was to marry the colors and textures of the interior with the exterior surroundings as the historic farmhouse sits in the most beautiful land surrounded by soaring cedars, abundant gardens and vineyards. Thank you @elizabethmessina for the beautiful photos and @bethprotass for styling

A look at the green accent wall in the dining room at @hoopesestategh . I wanted to have a statement color here and I painted the wall with “High Park” from @benjaminmoore . Swipe right to see more of my BTS tour where I share my philosophy that green is the other neutral (full length video in my reels). Another hot tip, “when you don’t have a window, use a mirror” 😉 Stunning photography by @elizabethmessina
Another beautiful view of the dining room at @hoopesestategh featuring these stunning ceramic pendant lights from @originalbtc . Photos by @elizabethmessina

The kitchen at @hoopesestategh turned out to be one of my favorite spaces in the project. Scroll through to see some of my favorite details like the “tumbleweed” tile from @fireclaytile, gold fixtures from @perrinandrowe of @houseofrohl and appliances from @cafeappliances Photography by @elizabethmessina styling by @bethprotass

The chicest little wine bar for @hoopesestategh featuring the under-counter beverage center from @cafeappliances which coordinates back to the full appliance suite in the kitchen. Swipe right to see my video tour of this space (also in my reels and stories) Photos by @elizabethmessina styling by @bethprotass

Creating a seamless flow between the indoors and outdoors was a top priority at @hoopesestategh . I was thrilled to refurbish the historic wraparound porch with beautiful new decking from @timbertech ‘s landmark collection in French White Oak. This pale shade of gray was so lovely with the both the white exterior and earthy pastel palette of the interior rooms. Photos by @elizabethmessina and styling by @bethprotass
Farm to table realness at @hoopesestategh photos by @elizabethmessina
The dreamiest poolside at @hoopesestategh thanks to @serenaandlily . I could lounge here every day all day! Photos by @elizabethmessina styling by @bethprotass

Ever wonder how I pick my paint colors? Especially how to select the perfect shade of white? Link in my stories to my interview with @housebeautiful and @benjaminmoore where I share all my tips to paint color selection! No matter what color you choose, quality is key! That’s why I love to use the Aura line from @benjaminmoore . Here is a shot from my project with @hoopesestategh featuring Benjamin Moore AF-15 “steam”. Photo by @elizabethmessina

The Fin pendant from @originalbtc was the perfect way to make an understated statement in the cottage size stairwell of @hoopesestategh I love the effect of textural white on white. It’s ethereal and dreamy! Photo by @elizabethmessina
One of my favorite bedrooms at the @hoopesestategh project. I chose to hang pendants on either side of the bed in lieu of bedside tables to maximize the space- do you like the effect?

The jewel box bathrooms at @hoopesestategh because good things can come in small packages! Think of fixtures like the jewelry in a room! Thank you @houseofrohl @housebeautiful Photos by @elizabethmessina styling @bethprotass
The twin bedroom at project @hoopesestategh decked out in the prettiest layered bedding from @serenaandlily photos by @elizabethmessina styling @bethprotass
Happy Holidays everyone! Wishing you all love and light ❤️ photo by @elizabethmessina

I’m obsessed with the front door at @hoopesestategh which was custom made by @simpsondoorco with a carved “H” for @hoopesvineyard Talk about making an entrance!
Photos by @elizabethmessina
This bay window at @hoopesestategh became one of the coziest nooks in the house, here layered up with pillows and throw from @anayahomeshop Photo by @elizabethmessina styling @bethprotass
A perfect spot to soak up the vacation vibes, this @houseofrohl bathtub became the star of this en suite bathroom at @hoopesestategh @housebeautiful Photography by @elizabethmessina

I love this wildflower of a kitchen at the @hoopesestategh project. This is a great example of how far you can go with just cosmetic changes- swipe right to the see the also adorable before version, who was simply ready for a 2022 update. Photo by @elizabethmessina

The dining room at @hoopesestategh I fell in love with these Christie pendant lights from @originalbtc which really pop against the garden inspired green accent wall painted in Benjamin Moore “High Park”. Photography by @elizabethmessina
Happy New Year everyone! Kicking off 2023 contemplating which came first, the chicken or the 🥚Photo by @elizabethmessina
Came across this portrait taken by @michaelbeauplet a few years back and just felt like sharing this “before kids” pic 😂

@annieselke is one of my go-to brands for bedding and rugs. This bedroom at @hoopesestategh is decked out in a few of my favorite @annieselke things like their Zhara rug (which you’ve seen at my house before), lush linen stripe bedding, and their natural linen drapes. Perfect for a hospitality project like this or a home with kids and dogs, these pieces have a luxury feel and stand up to high traffic. Photos by @elizabethmessina

Delighted to share my playroom on @dominomag today! Link to article in my stories! @crateandkids helped me bring this vision to life with the cutest kids size furniture (thank you @leannefordinteriors) and super chic woven storage bins. I converted my formal dining room into this space and it’s the first room you see when you enter my home, signaling kids are of equal importance to adults in our home.  Read all about my design choices in the article! Thank you @elizabethmessina for these gorgeous photos
Happy Friday! Love this cuddly resident of @hoopesestategh 📷@elizabethmessina

Nothing like cozying up with a good book. I’m currently obsessed with this vintage white Berber rug which I got from @saffronandpoe , one of my favorite home stores! Happy Valentine’s Day everyone! 📷 @elizabethmessina

My kids are going through their obsessed with FROZEN phase so I had to dig up this Elsa vibes photo for @voguemagazine to convince them I’m actually from “Erin-dale” (get it). Fun throwback to apt with @thelsd photography by @claiborneswansonfrank circa 2012

This bathroom makeover was a small but mighty triumph in the @hoopesestategh project. In addition to the dreamy lavender tiles I was particularly pleased with the @jamesmartinvanities sink vanity we were able to source (with a short lead time, thank you) from @fergusonshowrooms which is one my go-tos for bathroom and home renovation materials. Photo by @elizabethmessina #FergusonPartner #Ad

This week I’ll be sharing the before and after journey of my home office. This space required some vision and I couldn’t be happier with how it turned out. Up front and center is my super comfy @stayhomebody sofa where I love to catch a breath when I’m off duty from momming. This sofa is beyond plush and it’s modular design makes it a great investment as you can always add more pieces to evolve your layout over time. Swipe right to see the before pics of this space. Photos by @elizabethmessina

Here is my desk set up in my home office/ “she shed” (just heard that term for the first time yesterday). The heavenly velvet desk chair is from @mgbwhome and I found this desk from @jossandmain (love a quick ship find). The cool neutral palette was just what I was looking for. Photos by @elizabethmessina Swipe right to see the before pics

The kitchenette in my home office was a fun opportunity to create something playful and bright. I brought in this gorgeous faucet and Shaw’s sink from @houseofrohl to pop against a blush chevron tiled wall and fresh countertop. Swipe to see the before. 📷 by @elizabethmessina

The pitched ceilings in my office space created an interesting split bathroom with the shower on one side and the water closet on the other. When it comes to small bathroom design, I take a jewel box approach. Here that meant bringing in stellar fixtures from @houseofrohl and tile from @bedrosianstile 📷 by @elizabethmessina

Spring break, staycation edition. This is where you’ll find me if I catch some downtime, on my @stayhomebody sofa. The only risk is once you lay down, it’s so hard to get up again, the “sink in” factor is on point. Photography by @elizabethmessina

Now that you’ve seen my home office, I thought I’d show you the library and study space I created for my three boys. My oldest is in first grade and this was our first year having homework so setting up a space for him was fundamental in helping to lay down a good foundation of study habits, and of course the two little ones wanted to tag along. These media desk and chair sets from @Guidecraft_official were the perfect intersection of size, function and design.  The rotating book display is so cute and my baby loves to explore with it. You’re never to young to love reading! Photo by @elizabethmessina @Guidecraft_official, #Guidecraft, #Guidecraft_official, #Guidecraftfurniture

Check out my reels and stories today for more BTS at the @hoopesestategh project. Here I am with my life long friend Lindsey Hoopes! Thank you @fergusonshowrooms for all your support on this project. Photos by the lovely and talented @elizabethmessina #fergusonpartner

Since becoming a Mom, Mondays feel like what Sundays once were. A little recovery and a lot of productivity- which I personally find recharging. Can anyone relate? Thank goodness for my cozy home office sanctuary. I’m still obsessed with the vintage shag rug I found at @saffronandpoe See the shopping link in my stories 📷 @elizabethmessina
It’s a vibe. 📷 @elizabethmessina
Happy Friday! 📷 by @elizabethmessina
Some of my favorite residents from @hoopesestategh 📷 @elizabethmessina

Today, we’re taking you to Los Angeles, C.A. as Erin Fetherston, fashion and interior designer, shares her outdoor space. 

Known for her light and breezy design aesthetic, @erinfetherston chose our modern Santorini Collection to ground and define her outdoor spaces. Now, her whole family can enjoy their backyard in comfort all season long.
Happy Mother’s Day to my beautiful Mom and to all the mothers and mother figures out there- women make the world go round 📷 @elizabethmessina

This is where you’ll find me all season long...
With comfort & design in mind, choosing the @mgbwhome Santorini dining collection was a no-brainer

"My style is ethereal modern, but I'm really drawn to pieces with history." -Erin Fetherston (@erinfetherston)

With contemporary curves & textural rope details, our Santorini dining collection makes the perfect summer hosting spot.
Vintage white shag rug, need I say more? @saffronandpoe 📷 @elizabethmessina
Ten years and just getting started! Happy anniversary to my @gabrielsaporta , life with you is a blessing ❤️
When your outdoor furniture is set, summer can begin! I’m ready to go with this beautiful Santorini collection from @mgbwhome . Happy Memorial Day everyone!

My secret garden oasis features the Santorini outdoor furniture collection from @mgbwhome This collection was the perfect intersection of form and function for our backyard. Now if only June gloom would go away! #mgbwhome

I’m giddy with excitement over here guys, my home tour is live on @dominomag (link in bio and more on my stories). Thank you so much @dominomag @kateberryberry and @elizabethmessina for helping me share the journey of this home. I can’t wait to show you all the things.  @theeyeagency @theexpert glam by @thebeautyandstyleconcierge

I appreciate a clean, uncluttered approach to decorating which makes the details that much more important. For the finishing touches in my living room, @anastasiohome was the perfect match for my aesthetic- their stone dishes, magnificent dot box, and cruller bowl added the right node of earthiness and polish to this space and so far, have been unscathed by my cruising toddler and his older brothers. Photos by the one and only @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag If you haven’t checked out my full home tour yet, tap the link in bio!

These armchairs from @luluandgeorgia were one of the first pieces I committed to for our new home. I love how substantial they are which is something I look for when positioning chairs opposite a larger scale sofa as I did in our living room here. Scroll through to see a few of my other favorite @luluandgeorgia pieces in this project. Photos by @elizabethmessina

Stairway to heaven. Every time I walk into this entry I take a deep sigh and let that feeling of home wash over me. The opal chandelier from @corbettlighting is one of my favorite elements in this space- it feels like jewelry. One tip I always tell my clients with children is to “put your money on the ceiling”, meaning invest in a gorgeous light fixture which is generally out of reach of rambunctious littles and keep items lower to the ground less precious. Photography by @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag

A view into my kitchen taken from a spot where a wall once stood- this was the only structural change we did in our new home- opening the wall between the kitchen and what was previously the formal dining room (which we converted into a playroom). Space planning as a mom, I always want to maximize my view of the house from the kitchen sink (where I end up spending a lot of time). Scroll through for the before view. I’ll give you a full before and after kitchen tour soon! Photos by @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag

The oasis outside my home office featuring the Santorini collection from @mgbwhome This space is a nice grounding counterpoint to our light and airy interiors- that’s the fun of juxtaposition within one project.

Today I am honored to be featured in the latest issue of @cahomeanddesign . This article is appropriately titled “Race Against Time” as I got 80% of the house done in 9 weeks before giving birth, it none the less has taken me a good year to finish the last 20% (not that design can ever truly be finished) so it hasn’t felt that fast to me.  Like all projects and homes, this has been a true labor of love so it means a lot to me to share my story and journey with you.  Tap the link in bio or check my stories for the full article. Photography by @elizabethmessina Writing by @theshookones , glam by @thebeautyandstyleconcierge and extra special thanks to @aligrosslight
My story in @cahomeanddesign is on newsstands! Nothing like a good magazine spread to brighten my day! Photos by @elizabethmessina

The oak bok dining table and chairs from @ethnicraft was the perfect choice for our dining room. I love the modern lines and inviting quality of the oak. To my fellow parents out there- these chairs wipe down very easily and do a good job of containing wiggly children at meal time. Photo by @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag

Changing our kitchen countertops was one of the most transformative choices we made for our cosmetic kitchen renovation. The white surface reflects the natural lights and makes this space feel airy and expansive.  Scroll right to see the before photo. Thank you @cosentinousa for working with us on this very special project #cosentino #silestone #Dekton #sponsored Photo by @elizabethmessina

The Jasper sectional from @interiordefine in rose performance linen weave is the star of our family room. I’m obsessed with this earthy shade of blush which is standing up well in the face of high traffic. #howicustomizedit Photo by @elizabethmessina Use my special code: ERIN20 for 20% off at @interiordefine

Wildflower Farms certainly lived up to it’s name! I loved waking up to the view of this meadow each morning, it was exactly the reset I needed!Happy summer solstice! @wildflowerauberge @aubergeresorts

Just getting home from a whirlwind 3 day trip to the East Coast where we celebrated with old friends and had our first grown-up getaway in much too long. We had a blast but I must say it’s nice coming home to this summertime setup courtesy of @mgbwhome. Now if only the sunshine would come out!

Waking up in my cocoon of a bedroom with my @armadilloandco blush Malawi rug underfoot is the absolute best way to start the day. Something I love about @armadilloandco is that in addition to their sumptuous rugs they are a B corp and 10% of their profits go to their non-profit, the Armadillo Foundation, that brings health, education, and community structure to underprivileged communities. That is something to feel good about. Photo by @elizabethmessina

The warm, blushy cocoon that is my bedroom. When you live with three little boys and @gabrielsaporta you gotta get your pink in somewhere. Thank you @mgbwhome for making my bedroom dreams come true. Photo by @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag

If there is one adjective that has permeated my career, it’s “ethereal”. It’s not something I ever plan, it just kind of happens.  This mohair blanket from @serenaandlily was one of those lighter than air finds that perfectly topped off the sofa in my living room. I love this photo by @elizabethmessina

My living room, a little slice of heaven. One of the features that initially drew me to this home was the windows and natural light. That’s why one of the first design appointments I set was with @theshadestore . Here we layered tailored pleat drapes and Roman shades.  I like to mount drapery as high as I can to achieve a more vertical proportion on the windows. Swipe right to see the before pic! #loveyourwindows #theshadestore Photo by @elizabethmessina as seen in @cahomeanddesign

In all honesty, landing the art story for our new home was one of the more challenging parts of the design journey. At one point I was ready to try and paint my own canvases, but then I discovered the most beautiful works @burkedecor and I love them!

Spilling the tea on my bedding today.  I wanted my bedroom to feel luxe like a Parisian hotel suite but to also vibe with the relaxed spirit of our home. 
The unexpected pairing of linen and silk was the perfect combo to achieve this. Here, I have the “slipper pink” puff from @annieselke and coordinating pillowcases layered with their linen duvet set, topped of with this chinoiserie embroidered “Jolie” pillow from the @annieselke x @marieflaniganinteriors collab. Photo by @elizabethmessina

His and Hers approach to bedside styling- which do you like better? What’s for sure is this table lamp from @mgbwhome is a stunner! I chose the glass vase so the view of the window could shine through! Photo by @elizabethmessina
Staying simple sets the stage for natural light to do all kinds of magic. Swipe right to see the before of my “stairway to heaven”. Brandon sconce from @troylighting  Photo by @elizabethmessina

The Cate chandelier from @troylighting was my perfect find to crown our staircase. I love her traditional silhouette which feels fresh and modern in an all white textural finish. It also sets the decidedly relaxed tone I wanted for our second floor where all the kids bedrooms are. Swipe right to see what the previous owners had left behind. Photo by @elizabethmessina @hvlgroupintl
Tailored pleat drapes in luxe linen from @theshadestore make for the perfect dressing of my living room windows #loveyourwindows Photos by @elizabethmessina

I love the simplicity of our front entry. This oak spindle bench from @ethnicraft is the perfect hybrid of modern and traditional lines which works beautifully for the aesthetic of our home.  We use our back door for heavier traffic so this area is able to be light and airy for guests, making for q nice first look in the home. Photo by @elizabethmessina

Happy Summer Friday! Getting my dinner table set for friends tonight. For everyone who has asked, this is the Delano pendant from @hudsonvalleylighting and she is indeed obsession worthy! Photo by @elizabethmessina glam by @thebeautyandstyleconcierge

My kitchen makeover was an exercise in savvy renovating. In light of our 7 week timeframe, we kept our changes cosmetic but high impact by addressing the key surfaces: counters, floors, and walls. We installed this beautiful @cosentinousa countertop which brightened and modernized the overall feel of the space. By focusing on these surfaces, we were able to take advantage of the existing cabinetry (which is usually the longest and most expensive part of a kitchen reno) and I think it turned out beautifully. Swipe right to see the before image plus my reno notes. @cosentinousa @cosentinocitylosangeles@silestonebycosentino @dektobycosentin Photo by @elizabethmessina

More on the topic of savvy kitchen renovating…if you can find a way to work with your existing cabinetry, do it! It will save you a lot of time and money. Painting the cabinets can be a way to update them and my other tip is to upgrade the pulls and knobs. Here I use the egg knob and cup pulls from @emtek_products in polished nickel to refresh the cabinets in our kitchen. I love these modern classics that will stand the test of time. Photos by @elizabethmessina as seen in @dominomag

I always set my table with @yearandday and I’m obsessed with all their earthy pastel colors like this collection in Fog. They just launched an outdoor collection which I  cannot wait to get my hands on (I’ll be using it to upgrade my kids dinnerware since it’s not breakable). Photo by @elizabethmessina
Beautiful linen placemats and napkins from my favorite @annieselke complete this relaxed summertime tablescape. Photos by @elizabethmessina
Crafted for a long season in the fresh air, @erinfetherston is ready for outdoor hosting with our Santorini Collection. 🌤️✨

The many shades of @theshadestore I especially love the Parisian vibe I get from these Roman shades in the Nomad graphite stripe which I used to create a graphic accent in my family room #loveyourwindows Photos by @elizabethmessina

The powder room in our new home presented me with a fun design opportunity. It came with this black marble console and black and white basket weave tile floor (swipe right for the before pic). While these are not design choices I would have necessarily made from scratch, I wanted to lean into these elements while lightening the overall mood and making this space coherent with the rest of my house. The black and white crane wall paper was the perfect find to bridges these aesthetics! Another detail you can see in this photo is the updated door hinges I selected from @emtek to give these vintage doors a modern touch. Photo by @elizabethmessina

I love sharing my kitchen reno tips with you all. My strategy in this kitchen was to take advantage of the existing layout and cabinetry while upgrading all the surfaces and materials. Case in point, I brought in these stunning Georgian era bridge faucets from @perrinandrowe @houseofrohl to add some drama and elegance to the island and peninsula. I particularly love the height and curve of this fixture. Swipe right to see the “before” and let me know what you think of this upgrade. Photos by the lovely @elizabethmessina

My @silestonebycosentino “eternal noctis” countertops are one of my favorite design elements in my kitchen. They reflect the natural light and brighten the space. Thank you @cosentinousa @dektonbycosentino Photo by @elizabethmessina
Who’s hungry? I love this adorable play kitchen from @cocovillage Photo by @elizabethmessina
Sunday farmer’s market hydrangea score. Love my woven “Delano” pendant light from @hudsonvalleylighting Photo by @elizabethmessina
The happiest moments. Photo by @elizabethmessina

Another view of my living room showing off the many layers of neutrals and textures crowned by black accents in the light fixture and iron rods holding my luxe linen drapes by @theshadestore Photo by @elizabethmessina

I love a dramatic staircase and I felt this one had major potential when I first saw this house. I always strive to amplify natural light in a home so I chose a palette of whites from @benjaminmoore for this staircase make-over which naturally reflect and amplify the light (swipe right to see the before). Wall color is “cloud white” and trim is “dove wing”. I used “white dove” on the ceilings. I love this modern and sculptural “Brandon” wall sconce from @troylighting . And thank you @zimmermann for this fabulous ensemble. Photo by the one and only @elizabethmessina Make-up @thebeautyandstyleconcierge

When working with a neutral palette, layer textures to create depth. Here I piled on my favorite textural pillows from @the_citizenry to add warmth and coziness in my living room. Photo by @elizabethmessina
Riding this summer heat wave like 💃🏼Photo by @elizabethmessina

I took me quite awhile to find the right art for our space and I love the soft pastels and movement of this work which was an incredible find on @burkedecor and came mounted in this beautiful oak frame. Photo by @elizabethmessina

For all who have asked me about my toy storage, these cubbies are actually from @ikeausa . I used the 4 cube cubbies from their “Eket” system to create a wall of open shelving and I found the perfect woven bins to fit inside. Photo by @elizabethmessina
Artichokes are one of my favorite foods to eat and to style with. I love how to pop off my eternal noctis countertops from @silestonebycosentino @cosentinousa Photo by @elizabethmessina

A life well collected is a live well lived. I love this little corner of treasures in my living room. These 1960s French sun chairs were a great @1stdibs find. And this @zimmermann ensemble is everything. Photo by @elizabethmessina
Love these travertine nesting trays from @anastasiohome , I’m a bit of a minimalist when it comes to surface styling but these are the perfect finishing touch. Photo by @elizabethmessina
I love my garden oasis and these pieces from @mgbwhome “Santorini” outdoor collection.
Sunday snuggles 📷 @elizabethmessina
Making my bed with @annieselke 📷 @elizabethmessina

I love to use living things as art in my home- these sculptural flowers in a @burkedecor vase create interest and dimension, drawing the eye to this lovely corner of my living room 📷 @elizabethmessina

Something BIG is coming! Check my stories for a preview! Stay tuned for the full details later this week  @anthropologie @anthroliving 
📷 @elizabethmessina

I’m overjoyed to share my new home and fashion collection exclusively for @anthropologie has officially launched! This collection of furniture, rugs, lighting, decor and dresses has been a labor of love  I’ve worked on for the past year and half and I couldn’t be more excited that the time has finally here that I can share it with all of you! To the wonderful team at @anthropologie and @anthroliving , I’m full of gratitude that we could partner in bringing this incredibly special collection to life.  I love what we created and I can’t wait to hear what you all think of it!. Tap link it bio to shop!

Thank you all for the outpouring of support for the launch of my new home and fashion collection exclusively for @anthropologie . I am overjoyed to see it be so well received. Here I am next to one of my favorite pieces in the collection, the Dulcette buffet. Tap link in bio to shop my full collection! 📷 @andrewwerner @anthropologie @anthroliving

The Dulcette velvet sofa from my collection exclusively for @anthropologie is a rich mocha color with mauve undertones. I love it’s curvilinear form and fluted wooden base. The tree is really adding a vibe here too!  Tap link in bio to shop the full collection 📷 @bfa

Working with @anthropologie was a dream come true.
Our brands have aesthetic affinity, which made the overall creative exchange highly collaborative and expansive for us both.  When they first reached out to me about the possibility of collaborating, the timing could not have been better.  I had just moved into a new home and was deep in decorating mode, which as a designer is somewhat of an existential undertaking because every choice represents you creatively.  So having already spent several months immersed in my own dream world of furniture and home, I knew exactly what I wanted as well as what I couldn’t find, which is always a great space to create from.
Over the course of eighteen months, we worked diligently on each stage of design, from ideation to sourcing to in-person and virtual product reviews at the @anthropologie headquarters in Philadelphia.  I could not be more proud of what we created together. Swipe right to see some of my favorite living room furniture from this collection. 📷 @andrewwerner @anthroliving

I had the privilege of installing my new home collection exclusively for @anthropologie in this gorgeous NYC penthouse apartment (which is for sale in case you are in the market, thank you @asafbarlev ) I love seeing how these pieces translate in a light and airy environment. Which is your favorite? Tap link in bio to shop the full collection @anthroliving 📷 @andrewwerner

My exclusively for @anthropologie home collection is rooted in my favorite color palette- neutrals anchored by rich cocoa browns and earthy shades of blush. It looks great in a white wall setting as well as a room drenched in color. Swipe right to see another mood. Which is your vibe? 📷 @andrewwerner @anthroliving @rikkimenlo

I’ve been overwhelmed with grief these past 10 days. The stories, images, and accounts of what’s been happening in Israel and Gaza are heartbreaking. I haven’t felt like posting any of my usual content because pretty pictures of interiors seems like the last thing anyone needs to see right now. Today I dedicated several hours to nurturing my own nervous system to try and restore a sense of peace and calm within. I was reminded of the many beautiful messages I’ve received from you guys over the years telling me that my content helps you experience a moment of calm during a hectic day, so for that reason alone, I’m going to continue to share here as an expression of peace. We each have our own way of sharing light in the world so please know my heart and thoughts are with you all. May you all experience peace in your homes that can reverberate out into the world. One soul 📷 @elizabethmessina

How do you style a round coffee table? I have a more minimal hand when it comes to surface styling (mainly because I have a toddler at home) but when working with a round table, I envision a triangle inside the circle and arrange objects to more or less mark the three corners of a triangle inside the circle. Then it’s nice to use items of different heights to create depth and levels. Here is chose a clear vase so the eye can travel through to see the fireplace which is my focal point in this room. I have layered travertine trays from @anastasiohome and a stack of books with a beautiful spherical box. It looks simple, but it always takes a little bit of playing around with objects to get the right balance. 📷 @elizabethmessina
Gratitude. 📷 @elizabethmessina
